1) java me jo array unka ek drawback h wo dynamically apni size change nhi kr skte.
2) suppose ek array banaya student nam ka us class me 30 bacche ha to ek baccha nya add ho gaya to hum use array me add nhi kr skte.
    qki array ki size fixed hoti ha. unme hum size change nhi kr skte.

    ex : yha pr array index starts for 0 to 29. total 30 bachhe.
            but new student ko add krna hoga to  -->  String[] studentName = new String[31];
            yaha par 31 size dene padegi manually jo har bar possible nhi hai acchi practice bhi nhi hai.

        String[] studentName = new String[];
        studentName[0] = "Rakesh";

        studentName[29] = "Harish";

        // new student
        studentName[30] = "Raman";

3) dynamic array size allocation
    Arraylist<String> studentName = new ArrayList<>();
    studentName.add("Rakesh");
    --> it will add Rakesh ani size initially suppose n = 10 hoti
        size = n = 10;
        jb 11th element add kroge to,
        size = n + n/2 + 1;     --> dynamically evdhi size bnte
        aur purane wale array ko nye wale array me copy bhi kr dega.